{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Making child arrangements if you divorce or separate</h1>

      <p class="govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-1">Contents</p>
      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-body-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-8">
        <li>— <a href="#make-a-written-agreement" class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-underline">Make a written agreement</a></li>
        <li>— <a href="#if-you-need-help" class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-underline">If you need help to reach an agreement</a></li>
        <li>— <a href="#legally-binding" class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-underline">Make your agreement legally binding</a></li>
        <li>— <a href="#help-and-support" class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-underline">Help and support</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <h2 id="make-a-written-agreement" class="govuk-heading-l">Make a written agreement</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">You do not have to do any official paperwork if you agree about child arrangements.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">You can write down what you've agreed in a 'child arrangements plan' if you want a record.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">You can use this service to help you plan and agree on child arrangements. It creates a document which you can share with the other parent to ask for their agreement and suggestions.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">You can also use the service with the other parent to make a plan together.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Your safety</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">You should only use this service if:</p>
      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>you're confident that you and your ex-partner can make decisions together without putting yourself or the children in danger</li>
        <li>you do not feel pressured or intimidated into using it</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="govuk-body">If you think you or your children are at immediate risk of harm, call 999 and ask for the police. Find out <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/domestic-abuse-how-to-get-help" class="govuk-link">how to get help if you're experiencing domestic abuse</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">What the plan includes</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">You'll need to suggest details about how you plan to look after your children, such as:</p>
      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>when and where they spend time with each parent</li>
        <li>when and what other types of contact take place (phone calls, for example)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">When to use this service</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">You can use this service if you either:</p>
      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>have no child arrangements in place yet</li>
        <li>want to suggest changes to your existing arrangements</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Make your plan</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">Any plan you create using this service is not legally binding. The other parent does not have to do what it says and either of you can suggest changes to it at any time.</p>
        
        {% if includeWelshLanguage %}
          {% if getLocale() == 'cy' %}
            {{ govukInsetText({
              html: 'Mae\'r gwasanaeth hwn hefyd ar gael yn <a href="?lang=en" class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-underline">Saesneg (English)</a>'
            }) }}
          {% else %}
            {{ govukInsetText({
              html: 'This service is also available in <a href="?lang=cy" class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-underline">Welsh (Cymraeg)</a>'
            }) }}
          {% endif %}
        {% endif %}

      <form action="{{ paths.START }}" method="post" novalidate>
        <input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="{{ csrfToken }}" />
        {{
          govukButton({
            text: "Start now",
            classes: "govuk-button--start",
            isStartButton: true
          })
        }}
      </form>

      <p class="govuk-body">If you want to make changes to the plan, you can use the service again but you'll need to create a new plan.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">You can also <a href="{{ paths.DOWNLOAD_PAPER_FORM }}" class="govuk-link">download and fill in the child arrangements plan template (PDF, 0.5MB)</a>.</p>

      <h2 id="if-you-need-help" class="govuk-heading-m">If you need help to reach an agreement</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">A legal adviser can help you make a legally binding agreement or recommend <a href="https://www.gov.uk/looking-after-children-divorce/non-court-dispute-resolution" class="govuk-link">other ways to agree on child arrangements</a> outside of court. They can also tell you how much it costs.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">If you decide to go to court, you'll usually need to show you've attended a Mediation Information and Assessment Meeting (MIAM) with a mediator before you apply.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">You can usually get a voucher worth up to £500 to pay for family mediation through the Family Mediation Voucher Scheme, regardless of what you earn.</p>

      <h2 id="legally-binding" class="govuk-heading-m">Make your agreement legally binding</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">You can <a href="https://www.gov.uk/find-a-legal-adviser" class="govuk-link">get a legal adviser</a> to prepare a draft 'consent order'.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">You and your ex-partner both have to sign the draft consent order. You'll also need to get the draft consent order approved by the court.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">If the court approves your agreement, it will make a consent order, which is a legal document.</p>

      <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Get your consent order approved</h3>

      <p class="govuk-body">You or your ex-partner need to <a href="https://www.gov.uk/looking-after-children-divorce/apply-for-court-order" class="govuk-link">apply for a court order</a> to ask the court to approve your agreement and make it into a court order. Your legal adviser can help you with your application.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">You will not need to show that you've attended a MIAM with a mediator before you apply for a consent order to be made.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">Keep a copy of both the form and the draft consent order.</p>

      <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">After the court gets your paperwork</h3>

      <p class="govuk-body">There's usually no court hearing. A judge will approve your consent order to make it legally binding – but only if they think the arrangements reflect what is best for the children.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">If the judge does not agree with what is in your draft consent order they can: say that there should be a court hearing, or more evidence provided, to help decide what order should be made.</p>

      <h2 id="help-and-support" class="govuk-heading-m">Help and support</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">Get help and information from <a href="https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/" class="govuk-link">Citizens Advice</a>.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">Find support and guidance about child abuse and neglect on <a href="https://www.nspcc.org.uk/" class="govuk-link">NSPCC's website</a>.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">Find out how to <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/domestic-abuse-how-to-get-help" class="govuk-link">get help if you're a victim of domestic abuse</a>.</p>

    </div>

